The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 Calcutta, June 29: Jewellery worth Rs 5 lakh was stolen from a Middleton Row apartment this afternoon. Dr Shabnam Agarwal, who lives alone in the flat, found an almirah open and the jewellery missing when she returned from work around 4 pm.

 Police are suspecting a servant, aged about 28, who was employed by Agarwal only three days ago. The police are looking for the man. 

 Krishnagar: Six suspected Maoists have been arrested in connection with the killing of two CPM tribal leaders at Nadias Chandpur village on June 20. Lalu Biswas, Kaltu Biswas, Nikhil Biswas, Sunil Biswas, Niyamat Mahaldar and Ansarul Sheikh belonged to the action squad of the CPI (Maoist), Nadia superintendent of police R. Rajsekharan said.

 New Delhi: With around 140 trains scheduled to move faster, the railway has announced a new timetable offering the reduced journey time. Railway board chairman J.P. Batra said: The time taken for the journey will be reduced by one hour for 85 trains, by one to two hours for 31 trains, by two-three hours for 16 trains and over five hours for eight.

 Krishnagar: The Border Security Force has accused the Bangladesh Rifles of creating a tense situation along the border in south Bengal by opening unprovoked firing frequently. This has been severely disrupting the BSFs attempts to check smuggling and keep vigil on cross-border movement. 

 New Delhi: Election commissioner Naveen B. Chawla has told the Supreme Court that the poll panel cannot function independently if any political party or leader is allowed to seek removal of any of its members. BJP leader Jaswant Singh has sought Chawlas removal, alleging that he had abated improprieties during the Emergency and was a link between parties and the government. 

 Calcutta: Bengal chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee and the New York governor will soon sign a deal declaring Calcutta and New York sister cities, said Malcom Smith, New York state senator. The deal will offer collaboration in healthcare, education and economic development.




